                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 23, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>513. Dept wishes to be sure that implications of its 510 Apr 22 are not
                    misunderstood: It assumes you will not depart from China before communicating
                    with it for final confirmatory instructions unless communications are entirely
                    severed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
